  "body": "This is a follow up to #15381, specifically @sebmarkbage's comment regarding the mismatch in the missing hit target element and the usage of `pointer-events: none`. This now re-applies the hit slop element and its hit slop properties, with the addition of making `pointer-events: none` so they get excluded in hit target calculations till after hydration has completed. This should hopefully reduce the amount of reflows to the DOM too.\r\n\r\nTo get hydration updates for `TouchHitTarget` a special `hydrateTouchHitTarget` prop gets passed around, otherwise ReactDOM doesn't correctly set `pointer-events` to `auto` after.",
